subSubSection.paragraph:
Colouration in preservation:
Dorsum dark brown to grey-brown, unpatterned (
Fig. 2
); venter slightly paler than dorsum; scales of head and neck dark brown, each edged by a brighter border; remaining body scales, particularly on the ventral side, light brown with darker marbling; nuchal and body bands absent; tip of snout, supralabials, throat, hind limbs and preanal region slightly lighter, cream coloured (
Fig. 4A
).
